attaches to hedgehogs. Monopoles, the analogous defects of charge or generic\nU(1) currents, may bind to hedgehogs via Zeeman effect, or effectively emerge\nin purely magnetic systems. The latter can lead to spin liquids with different\ntopological orders than that of the RVB spin liquid. Charge fractionalization\nof quarks in atomic nuclei is also seen as possibly arising from the\ncharge-hedgehog attachment.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 8 Jul 2019 18:00:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 16 Jun 2020 17:35:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-06-17"}
