miniscent of the behaviors of a fragmenting comet D/1999 S4 (LINEAR). The\nmost plausible scenario for the observed polarimetric properties of 252P/LINEAR\nwould be an ejection of predominantly large, compact dust particles from the\ndesiccated surface layer. We conjecture that the more intense solar heating\nthat the comet has received in the near-Earth orbit would cause the paucity of\nsmall, fluffy dust particles around the nucleus of the comet.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 9 Jul 2019 03:10:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-18"}
